As for the actual topic of the thread, I'm with the folks who believe that marriage is a commitment between two people.  The nature of that commitment, however, is up to them entirely.  Marriage can be as much a legal state as an emotional one, and sex can be as much a recreational activity as it is an emotional act - and if (BIG if) both parties are on the same page about what type of relationship they have, and choose to branch out, more power to them.  <br>
